OL,3,CStudy finds 'alarming' inequality in
OL,4,Ccare for chronic lung disease patients
OL,6,FResearchers found the risk of death
OL,7,Famong the most deprived patients was
OL,8,F36% higher compared with the least
OL,9,Fdeprived.
OL,11,FWhen factors such as smoking, gender,
OL,12,Fage and distance to hospital were
OL,13,Fconsidered, the risk of death was
OL,14,Fstill 39%. Patients who lived further
OL,15,Faway from respiratory clinics also had
OL,16,Fa worse survival rate.
