OL,3,CStudy finds 'alarming' inequality in
OL,4,Ccare for chronic lung disease patients
OL,6,FThere was a 34% increased risk of
OL,7,Fdeath among patients living furthest
OL,8,Faway compared with those living
OL,9,Fclosest. When other factors were
OL,10,Fconsidered, the risk of death was
OL,11,Fstill 29%.
OL,13,FProfessor Andrew Wilson, of UEA's
OL,14,FNorwich Medical School, said: "This is
OL,15,Fthe first time that social deprivation
OL,16,Fand travelling distance to hospital
OL,17,Fhas been linked to survival for people
OL,18,Fwith pulmonary fibrosis living in the
OL,19,FUK.
