OL,3,CStudy finds 'alarming' inequality in
OL,4,Ccare for chronic lung disease patients
OL,6,F"People planning hospital services for
OL,7,Fpeople for pulmonary fibrosis should
OL,8,Fconsider those living far from
OL,9,Fhospitals and those from poorer
OL,10,Fbackgrounds to make sure these people
OL,11,Fget the care they need."
OL,13,FThe study also found that 40% of
OL,14,Fpatients had symptoms for more than
OL,15,Ftwo years before being seen in a
OL,16,Fspecialist clinic. It is estimated
OL,17,Fthat about 5,000 people are diagnosed
OL,18,Fwith IPF each year in the UK.
